<subSubSection id="C328652AB461FFFFFF2F591CE1A4F868" pageId="0" pageNumber="195" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8D36A1B461FFFFFF2F591CE1A4F868" blockId="0.[136,1452,1792,1922]" pageId="0" pageNumber="195">
<emphasis id="B946EAB3B461FFFFFF2F591CE5F5F8B7" bold="true" box="[136,235,1863,1885]" pageId="0" pageNumber="195">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: From its putative closest ally, 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D22B461FFFFFDB05913E7CDF8B7" authorityName="Regel" authorityYear="1861" baseAuthorityName="Bunge" baseAuthorityYear="1831" box="[535,723,1864,1885]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Pulsatilla" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="0" pageNumber="195" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chinensis">
<emphasis id="B946EAB3B461FFFFFDB05913E7CDF8B7" box="[535,723,1864,1885]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="195">Pulsatilla chinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13092A24B461FFFFFD465913E602F8B4" box="[737,796,1864,1886]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1992,2014]" captionTargetBox="[244,1344,190,1968]" captionTargetId="figure-20@4.[240,1348,190,1968]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pulsatilla chinensis in the wild (Dahei Mountain, Dalian, Liaoning province, north-east China). A. Habit. B. Basal leaves (left: abaxial side; right: adaxial side). C. Flower (top view). D. Sepals (left: adaxial side; right: abaxial side). E. Flower with the sepals removed. F. Stamens. G. Achenes. Photographed by T.T. Zhang." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358205" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358205/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="195">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
), the new species 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D22B461FFFFFC6D5913E12CF8B7" authorityName="L. Xu &amp; T. G. Kang" authorityYear="2022" box="[970,1074,1864,1885]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Pulsatilla" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="0" pageNumber="195" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="saxatilis">
<emphasis id="B946EAB3B461FFFFFC6D5913E12CF8B7" box="[970,1074,1864,1885]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="195">P. saxatilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguishable by having light blue, whitish-blue or white (vs. violet) sepals and persistent styles 
<quantity id="4CCA9B44B461FFFFFCA05937E67EF86B" box="[775,864,1900,1922]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="0" pageNumber="195" unit="cm" value="2.25" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="2.0">2–2.5 cm</quantity>
(vs. 
<quantity id="4CCA9B44B461FFFFFC285937E6E2F86B" box="[911,1020,1900,1922]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="6.5" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="0" pageNumber="195" unit="cm" value="5.0" valueMax="6.5" valueMin="3.5">3.5–6.5 cm</quantity>
) long (see 
<tableCitation id="C6B0031AB461FFFFFBC25937E1B5F868" box="[1125,1195,1900,1922]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="5.[136,224,1661,1685]" captionTargetBox="[144,1400,1699,2079]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="TABLE 1. Morphological comparison between Pulsatilla chinensis and P. saxatilis." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF4D6629B464FFFAFF2F5826E113F97F" pageId="0" pageNumber="195" tableUuid="DF4D6629B464FFFAFF2F5826E113F97F">Table 1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C328652AB461FFFAFF2F59EBE7EBFE87" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="200" pageId="0" pageNumber="195" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8D36A1B461FFFEFF2F59EBE7C6FE86" blockId="0.[136,1452,1968,2067]" lastBlockId="1.[136,1452,158,365]" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="196" pageId="0" pageNumber="195">
<emphasis id="B946EAB3B461FFFFFF2F59EBE40CF820" bold="true" box="[136,274,1968,1994]" pageId="0" pageNumber="195">Description</emphasis>
:—Perennial herb, 
<quantity id="4CCA9B44B461FFFFFE4259EBE75BF821" box="[485,581,1968,1995]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="0" pageNumber="195" unit="cm" value="14.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="9.0">9–20 cm</quantity>
tall. Rhizome 
<quantity id="4CCA9B44B461FFFFFD4159EBE653F821" box="[742,845,1968,1995]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="0" pageNumber="195" unit="cm" value="0.75" valueMax="1.0" valueMin="0.5">0.5–1 cm</quantity>
in diameter. Basal leaves 6–11, leaf blade ovate, 2–3.5 × 
<quantity id="4CCA9B44B461FFFFFF38598FE417F805" box="[159,265,2004,2031]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="0" pageNumber="195" unit="cm" value="2.25" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.5">1.5–3 cm</quantity>
, 3–foliolate or ternate-pinnate. Central leaflet long petiolulate, 
<quantity id="4CCA9B44B461FFFFFC6D598FE12CF805" box="[970,1074,2004,2031]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="0" pageNumber="195" unit="cm" value="1.25" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="0.5">0.5–2 cm</quantity>
long, cordate, 3–foliolate, central segment stipitate and deeply 3–lobed, ultimate lobes cuniform, 
<quantity id="4CCA9B44B461FFFFFCFC59A3E6C7F7F9" box="[859,985,2040,2067]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="0" pageNumber="195" unit="cm" value="0.44999999999999996" valueMax="0.6" valueMin="0.3">0.3–0.6 cm</quantity>
wide, apically 2–or 3–toothed, abaxially sparsely long pilose, adaxially glabrous; petiole 
<quantity id="4CCA9B44B460FFFEFD015EC5E60FFF53" box="[678,785,158,185]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.75" metricValueMax="7.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" unit="cm" value="4.75" valueMax="7.5" valueMin="2.0">2–7.5 cm</quantity>
, densely white villose. Scapes solitary or 2, occasionally 3, erect, white villose. Involucral bracts 3 or 4, 1– 
<quantity id="4CCA9B44B460FFFEFD3C5E99E7F4FF37" box="[667,746,194,221]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" unit="cm" value="2.4">2.4 cm</quantity>
long, connate and tubular at base, apically palmately 3–lobed, apical palmate lobes lanceolate, abaxially densely long pilose. Flowers solitary, erect, 
<quantity id="4CCA9B44B460FFFEFBE75EBDE18CFEEB" box="[1088,1170,230,257]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" unit="cm" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4 cm</quantity>
in diameter; sepals 6–11, light blue, whitish–blue or white, oblong-ovate, 1.5–2.5 × 
<quantity id="4CCA9B44B460FFFEFC835F51E6B8FECF" box="[804,934,266,293]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="14.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" unit="cm" value="0.8999999999999999" valueMax="1.4" valueMin="0.4">0.4–1.4 cm</quantity>
, abaxially puberulent; stamens numerous, ca. 1/2 as long as sepals; carpels numerous, style yellow-green, stigma pale violet. Achenes 
<quantity id="4CCA9B44B460FFFEFBC95F75E1FFFEA3" box="[1134,1249,302,329]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" unit="mm" value="2.75" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.5">2.5–3 mm</quantity>
long, long pilose. Persistent styles 
<quantity id="4CCA9B44B460FFFEFEE45F09E4B5FE87" box="[323,427,338,365]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" unit="cm" value="2.25" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="2.0">2–2.5 cm</quantity>
long, sparsely long pilose.
</paragraph>
