<emphasis id="B946EAB3B464FFFAFF1A5CCDE4B7FD5A" bold="true" box="[189,425,662,688]" pageId="5" pageNumber="200">Conservation status</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D22B464FFFAFE6A5CCDE782FD5A" authorityName="L. Xu &amp; T. G. Kang" authorityYear="2022" box="[461,668,662,688]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Pulsatilla" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="5" pageNumber="200" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="saxatilis">
<emphasis id="B946EAB3B464FFFAFE6A5CCDE782FD5A" box="[461,668,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="200">Pulsatilla saxatilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently known only from its 
<typeStatus id="54898803B464FFFAFBAD5CCCE124FD5B" box="[1034,1082,663,689]" pageId="5" pageNumber="200">type</typeStatus>
locality, with its distribution area being very small, although the population we observed in 2015 consisted of numerous individuals, and the habitat was in good condition, not disturbed by human activities. The conservation status of 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D22B464FFFAFBB65C84E194FD12" authorityName="L. Xu &amp; T. G. Kang" authorityYear="2022" box="[1041,1162,734,760]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Pulsatilla" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="5" pageNumber="200" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="saxatilis">
<emphasis id="B946EAB3B464FFFAFBB65C84E194FD12" box="[1041,1162,734,760]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="200">P. saxatilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may better be considered as “Endangered” (IUCN Standards and Petitions Committee 2019).
</paragraph>
